{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_27","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc 'curl -sS -X PUT -H "Authorization: Bearer $PAPERCLIP_API_KEY" -H "X-Paperclip-Run-Id: $PAPERCLIP_RUN_ID" -H "Content-Type: application/json" "$PAPERCLIP_API_URL/api/issues/$PAPERCLIP_TASK_ID/documents/plan" -d @- <<'"'JSON'
{
  \"title\": \"Plan\",
  \"format\": \"markdown\",
  \"body\": \"# Plan\\n\\n## Objective\\nDeliver one production-ready vertical slice for the Investment Assistant covering UI -> API -> data retrieval -> analysis output, with tests and observability, in one focused engineering session.\\n\\n## Session Focus (Now)\\nShip the first user-visible slice end-to-end:\\n- A single user question can be submitted from UI\\n- Backend validates request and orchestrates analysis flow\\n- Data source fetch + model response return structured result\\n- User sees final answer plus confidence/source summary\\n\\n## Definition of Done\\n- Happy path works from frontend to backend in local/staging environment.\\n- API contract is versioned and documented for this slice.\\n- Automated tests cover request validation, core orchestration logic, and UI rendering of success/error states.\\n- Observability baseline exists: request id tracing, structured logs, and latency/error metrics for this flow.\\n\\n## Scope\\n### In scope (this issue)\\n1. **Vertical slice target**\\n- Implement one concrete workflow: submit investment question -> generate analysis response.\\n- Restrict to one supported asset type and one response template for v1 slice.\\n\\n2. **API + backend orchestration**\\n- Finalize endpoint contract for this slice.\\n- Implement validation, service orchestration, and deterministic error model.\\n- Add integration boundary for data provider + model provider with clear failure handling.\\n\\n3. **Frontend integration**\\n- Wire one UI entry point to the new endpoint.\\n- Handle loading, success, and failure UX states without placeholder-only behavior.\\n\\n4. **Quality + observability**\\n- Add focused unit/integration tests for slice logic and API behavior.\\n- Add UI tests for submission and result rendering.\\n- Add structured log fields (requestId, user/session key hash, timing, failure reason).\\n\\n### Out of scope (later issues)\\n- Multi-step portfolio workflows, watchlists, and advanced charting.\\n- Full prompt optimization and multi-model routing.\\n- Deep SRE hardening beyond baseline telemetry for this slice.\\n\\n## Implementation Sequence\\n1. Freeze endpoint contract and response schema for this single slice.\\n2. Implement backend orchestrator + data/model adapters with test doubles.\\n3. Integrate UI flow and user-state handling.\\n4. Add test coverage and observability instrumentation.\\n5. Validate in staging-like environment and publish execution evidence.\\n\\n## Risks and Mitigations\\n- **Risk:** external API/model instability causes flaky results.\\n  - **Mitigation:** isolate provider interfaces, add timeout/retry policy, and deterministic fallback error responses.\\n- **Risk:** contract drift between UI and backend.\\n  - **Mitigation:** lock typed schema and add contract tests in CI.\\n- **Risk:** low debugging visibility in first release.\\n  - **Mitigation:** enforce request-id propagation and structured log fields from day one.\\n\\n## Handoff to Founding Engineer\\nExecute this as one implementation slice and return with:\\n- changed file list by layer (UI/API/domain/tests)\\n- test evidence (commands and pass output summary)\\n- sample request/response payload for the shipped flow\\n- observability evidence (log/metric fields captured)\\n- open risks needing CEO prioritization\\n\"
}
